Nine of the most famous lighthouses around the world include:

1. Eddystone Lighthouse, England: This historic lighthouse is situated on a treacherous rocky reef in the English Channel and has gone through multiple iterations since its original construction.

2. Bell Rock Lighthouse, Scotland: Built in 1810, this tower has withstood harsh waves and storms for over two centuries and still operates today.

3. Cape Hatteras Light Station, North Carolina, USA: The tallest brick-built lighthouse in North America at 210 feet high serves as a navigational aid along the treacherous coastline known as "The Graveyard of the Atlantic."

4. Peggy's Point Lighthouse (Peggy's Cove), Nova Scotia, Canada: An iconic symbol of maritime Canada that attracts thousands of tourists each year.

5. La Jument Lighthouse, Brittany, France: Known for having one of the wildest waters to protect due to frequent violent waves crashing against it during heavy weather conditions.

6. Tower Of Hercules: A Roman-era structure located near Corunna in Galicia stands as an example of ancient lighthouses resembling modern designs. It's believed that it was built by Romans between 110-150 AD

7) Alexandria Pharos,a light station constructed after Alexander The Great’s death upon order his General Ptolemy I Soter ,it stood about approximative five hundred fifty feet tall,encompassed statue human figure holding torchlight .It lasted till XIV century when earthquake destructed 

8) Portland Head Light-Maine United States-South Portland city hosts this beautiful landmark which caught artists photographers attention from XIX th century.Portland head lamp constructed beginning nineteenth century once commissioned George Washington
